# Contributing

---

## Branching Convention

All work should happen on a short-lived feature branch, merged into `main` via a pull request.

**Branch naming format:** `<type>/<short-description>`

| Prefix | Use for |
|---|---|
| `feat/` | New template, prompt template, bundle, or feature |
| `fix/` | Bug fix or correction to existing content |
| `docs/` | Documentation-only change |
| `ci/` | GitHub Actions workflow or script change |
| `chore/` | Maintenance, renaming, or housekeeping |
| `copilot/` | AI-generated branches created by GitHub Copilot |

Examples: `feat/sprint-review-template`, `fix/csv-type-validation`, `docs/update-readme`

**Rules:**
- Branch off `main` and keep branches short-lived (merge or close within days, not weeks)
- One logical change per branch — avoid bundling unrelated changes
- Delete branches after the PR is merged

---

## Commit Message Convention

This repository follows [Conventional Commits](https://www.conventionalcommits.org/):

```
<type>(<optional scope>): <short summary in imperative mood>
```

**Types:**

| Type | Use for |
|---|---|
| `feat` | New template, prompt template, bundle, or feature |
| `fix` | Bug fix or correction |
| `docs` | Documentation changes only |
| `ci` | CI/CD workflow or script changes |
| `chore` | Maintenance, renaming, or housekeeping |
| `refactor` | Code restructuring without behaviour change |

**Examples:**
```
feat: add sprint-review template
fix: correct TYPE validation in validate-templates workflow
docs: update CONTRIBUTING with branching guide
ci: add release workflow for automated tagging
chore: rename certification-exam to exam-certification-workflow
```

**Rules:**
- Use the imperative mood in the summary ("add", not "added" or "adds")
- Keep the summary line under 72 characters
- No period at the end of the summary line
- Avoid generic messages like "Update file" or "Fix stuff"

### Pull Request Titles

PR titles are used as the squash-merge commit message on `main`. They must follow the same Conventional Commits format as individual commit messages.

### Merge Strategy

Use **Squash and merge** when merging PRs into `main`. This keeps the `main` history clean and meaningful — one commit per logical change, with the PR title as the commit message.

---

## Templates must:

- Include:
  - template.csv
  - meta.yml
  - README.md
- Avoid hardcoded due dates
- Use consistent section formatting
- Follow naming conventions

Optional meta.yml fields:

- project_color: Todoist color name (berry_red, red, orange, yellow, olive_green, lime_green, green, mint_green, teal, sky_blue, light_blue, blue, grape, violet, lavender, magenta, salmon, charcoal, grey, taupe)

Before adding a new template:

- Open an issue describing the workflow
- Define acceptance criteria
- Clarify reuse potential

---

## Prompt Templates

Prompt templates must:

- Live under `prompt-templates/{slug}/` (kebab-case folder name)
- Include:
  - `prompt.md`
  - `meta.yml`
  - `README.md`
- Use `{{placeholder}}` syntax for all input variables
- Be provider-agnostic (must work with any instruction-following LLM)
- Define a clear output schema with required and optional sections
- Include at least one worked example (input + expected output)

`meta.yml` required keys:

- `name:`
- `slug:` (must match the folder name exactly)
- `description:`
- `category:`
- `tags:`
- `version:`
- `inputs:` (list of placeholder variable names, without braces)

Before adding a new prompt template:

- Open an issue describing the use case and target workflow
- Define the input variables and expected output schema
- Confirm the prompt works end-to-end with at least one LLM before submitting

---

## Documentation Sync

When adding a new template or prompt template, update the following:

- `index.md` — add a row to the appropriate section of the catalogue table
- `.github/workflows/create-todoist-project.yml`:
  - For CSV templates: add the slug to the `options` list under `inputs.template`
  - For prompt templates: add the slug to the `options` list under `inputs.prompt_template`
- `README.md` — update any references if the new template changes usage instructions
